{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/pages/gatsby-blog-tutorial/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"codingwbeto"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"abd35576-2553-5b35-8090-ce9444f324ea","excerpt":"In this tutorial we will go over how to create a blog using gatsby. Table of Contents Installation Run a gatsby preview server Edit src/pages/index.js Edit one…","html":"<p>In this tutorial we will go over how to create a blog using gatsby.</p>\n<h3>Table of Contents</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"#installation\">Installation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#run-a-gatsby-preview-server\">Run a gatsby preview server</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#edit-src/pages/indexjs\">Edit src/pages/index.js</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#edit-one-of-the-blog-posts\">Edit one of the blog posts</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#understand-how-gatsby-creates-our-blog-posts\">Understand how gatsby creates our blog posts</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#test-our-understanding-how-gatsby-creates-our-blog-posts\">Test our understanding how gatsby creates our blog posts</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#connect-a-headless-cms\">Connect a headless cms</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#use-Github-to-host-your-blog-for-free\">Use Github to host your blog for free</a></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Installation<a name=\"installation\"></a></h3>\n<p>Use a curl command to install <a href=\"https://brew.sh/\" target=\"_blank\">Homebrew</a> inside the /bin/bash directory <br/></p>\n<h6>Open your terminal and run</h6>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">/bin/bash <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-c</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-fsSL</span> https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<h6>Use brew to install Node</h6>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">brew install node </code></pre></div>\n<h6>Use node to install gatsby</h6>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm install gatsby</code></pre></div>\n<h6>Use npm to initialize gatsby project</h6>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm init gatsby</code></pre></div>\n<p>Change into your project directory</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">cd gatsby-starter-blog</code></pre></div>\n<p>This is what your project should look like</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">my-gatsby-site/\n▸ node_modules/\n▸ public/\n▸ src/\n  gatsby-config.js\n  package-lock.json\n  package.json\n  README.md</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Run a Gatsby preview server <a name=\"run-a-gatsby-preview-server\"></a></h3>\n<h6>Lets see what this gatsby starter site looks like, run the following command</h6>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm run develop</code></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/reponame/static/9b5f38830a0d8f679d6524d2c2ae7c2d/644c5/starterSite.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.65822784810127%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"npm run develop\"\n        title=\"npm run develop\"\n        src=\"/reponame/static/9b5f38830a0d8f679d6524d2c2ae7c2d/828fb/starterSite.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/reponame/static/9b5f38830a0d8f679d6524d2c2ae7c2d/ff44c/starterSite.jpg 158w,\n/reponame/static/9b5f38830a0d8f679d6524d2c2ae7c2d/a6688/starterSite.jpg 315w,\n/reponame/static/9b5f38830a0d8f679d6524d2c2ae7c2d/828fb/starterSite.jpg 630w,\n/reponame/static/9b5f38830a0d8f679d6524d2c2ae7c2d/0ede0/starterSite.jpg 945w,\n/reponame/static/9b5f38830a0d8f679d6524d2c2ae7c2d/3ac88/starterSite.jpg 1260w,\n/reponame/static/9b5f38830a0d8f679d6524d2c2ae7c2d/644c5/starterSite.jpg 1440w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Edit src/pages/index.js <a name=\"edit-src/pages/index.js\"></a></h3>\n<p>When you ran the Gatsby preview server, it says to edit src/pages/index.js so lets give that a try.</p>\n<p>Lets start off by deleting the congradulations message and the line it says to edit the src/pages/index.js file</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/reponame/static/c54629316ef636d29ab2b66c17ef2c48/669cd/editingIndex.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 65.18987341772153%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Editing src/pages/index.js\"\n        title=\"Editing src/pages/index.js\"\n        src=\"/reponame/static/c54629316ef636d29ab2b66c17ef2c48/f058b/editingIndex.png\"\n        srcset=\"/reponame/static/c54629316ef636d29ab2b66c17ef2c48/c26ae/editingIndex.png 158w,\n/reponame/static/c54629316ef636d29ab2b66c17ef2c48/6bdcf/editingIndex.png 315w,\n/reponame/static/c54629316ef636d29ab2b66c17ef2c48/f058b/editingIndex.png 630w,\n/reponame/static/c54629316ef636d29ab2b66c17ef2c48/40601/editingIndex.png 945w,\n/reponame/static/c54629316ef636d29ab2b66c17ef2c48/78612/editingIndex.png 1260w,\n/reponame/static/c54629316ef636d29ab2b66c17ef2c48/669cd/editingIndex.png 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Lets go ahead and add a navbar</p>\n<p>This is a good place to introduce what React calls components, all your pages will have a navbar. Why hardcode that navbar on every page? Doing that will eventually give you unnessary headacks from silly things such as typo errors. The idea behind React components is so that you write the code once and just import it in all your pages.</p>\n<p>Create a file inside src/components/ name it Navbar.js</p>\n<p>You have two diffrent ways you can create this component, using a regular function</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/reponame/static/d91e80309e61a549bdea675459cb6db2/de0bd/navComponentFunction.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 34.177215189873415%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Nav Component Function\"\n        title=\"Nav Component Function\"\n        src=\"/reponame/static/d91e80309e61a549bdea675459cb6db2/f058b/navComponentFunction.png\"\n        srcset=\"/reponame/static/d91e80309e61a549bdea675459cb6db2/c26ae/navComponentFunction.png 158w,\n/reponame/static/d91e80309e61a549bdea675459cb6db2/6bdcf/navComponentFunction.png 315w,\n/reponame/static/d91e80309e61a549bdea675459cb6db2/f058b/navComponentFunction.png 630w,\n/reponame/static/d91e80309e61a549bdea675459cb6db2/40601/navComponentFunction.png 945w,\n/reponame/static/d91e80309e61a549bdea675459cb6db2/78612/navComponentFunction.png 1260w,\n/reponame/static/d91e80309e61a549bdea675459cb6db2/de0bd/navComponentFunction.png 2238w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Or by using an arrow function</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/reponame/static/9a07ae22fda002344d3281a8f4f56c7b/6660b/navComponentArrowFunction.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 31.645569620253163%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Nav Component Arrow Function\"\n        title=\"Nav Component Arrow Function\"\n        src=\"/reponame/static/9a07ae22fda002344d3281a8f4f56c7b/f058b/navComponentArrowFunction.png\"\n        srcset=\"/reponame/static/9a07ae22fda002344d3281a8f4f56c7b/c26ae/navComponentArrowFunction.png 158w,\n/reponame/static/9a07ae22fda002344d3281a8f4f56c7b/6bdcf/navComponentArrowFunction.png 315w,\n/reponame/static/9a07ae22fda002344d3281a8f4f56c7b/f058b/navComponentArrowFunction.png 630w,\n/reponame/static/9a07ae22fda002344d3281a8f4f56c7b/40601/navComponentArrowFunction.png 945w,\n/reponame/static/9a07ae22fda002344d3281a8f4f56c7b/78612/navComponentArrowFunction.png 1260w,\n/reponame/static/9a07ae22fda002344d3281a8f4f56c7b/6660b/navComponentArrowFunction.png 2278w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I sprinkled some bootstrap to quickly style this Nav component, create a file called gatsby-browser.js in the root folder of your project. Here is were you import your css. It is best practice to always use normalize.css because diffrent browsers interpret styling in there own ways and this makes sure your styling is consitant in every browser.</p>\n<p>To get bootstrap just install it using <code class=\"language-text\">npm install bootstrap</code></p>\n<p>To get normalize.css just install it using <code class=\"language-text\">npm install normalize.css</code></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/reponame/static/eb64abfd2937e87f16e85a4898b3afae/5fada/gatsby-browser.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 29.11392405063291%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Gatsby Browser Page\"\n        title=\"Gatsby Browser Page\"\n        src=\"/reponame/static/eb64abfd2937e87f16e85a4898b3afae/f058b/gatsby-browser.png\"\n        srcset=\"/reponame/static/eb64abfd2937e87f16e85a4898b3afae/c26ae/gatsby-browser.png 158w,\n/reponame/static/eb64abfd2937e87f16e85a4898b3afae/6bdcf/gatsby-browser.png 315w,\n/reponame/static/eb64abfd2937e87f16e85a4898b3afae/f058b/gatsby-browser.png 630w,\n/reponame/static/eb64abfd2937e87f16e85a4898b3afae/40601/gatsby-browser.png 945w,\n/reponame/static/eb64abfd2937e87f16e85a4898b3afae/78612/gatsby-browser.png 1260w,\n/reponame/static/eb64abfd2937e87f16e85a4898b3afae/5fada/gatsby-browser.png 1706w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Lets import this component into our homepage <code class=\"language-text\">src/pages/index.js</code></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/reponame/static/3c618844eb5f78ce6a68ecd964934ee5/5522e/importingNav.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 30.37974683544304%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Importing Nav\"\n        title=\"Importing Nav\"\n        src=\"/reponame/static/3c618844eb5f78ce6a68ecd964934ee5/f058b/importingNav.png\"\n        srcset=\"/reponame/static/3c618844eb5f78ce6a68ecd964934ee5/c26ae/importingNav.png 158w,\n/reponame/static/3c618844eb5f78ce6a68ecd964934ee5/6bdcf/importingNav.png 315w,\n/reponame/static/3c618844eb5f78ce6a68ecd964934ee5/f058b/importingNav.png 630w,\n/reponame/static/3c618844eb5f78ce6a68ecd964934ee5/40601/importingNav.png 945w,\n/reponame/static/3c618844eb5f78ce6a68ecd964934ee5/78612/importingNav.png 1260w,\n/reponame/static/3c618844eb5f78ce6a68ecd964934ee5/5522e/importingNav.png 2680w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Your page should now look like this</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/reponame/static/fac13ecd4e440d8692bc98b18bb7f5ca/669cd/previewNav.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.65822784810127%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Preview Nav\"\n        title=\"Preview Nav\"\n        src=\"/reponame/static/fac13ecd4e440d8692bc98b18bb7f5ca/f058b/previewNav.png\"\n        srcset=\"/reponame/static/fac13ecd4e440d8692bc98b18bb7f5ca/c26ae/previewNav.png 158w,\n/reponame/static/fac13ecd4e440d8692bc98b18bb7f5ca/6bdcf/previewNav.png 315w,\n/reponame/static/fac13ecd4e440d8692bc98b18bb7f5ca/f058b/previewNav.png 630w,\n/reponame/static/fac13ecd4e440d8692bc98b18bb7f5ca/40601/previewNav.png 945w,\n/reponame/static/fac13ecd4e440d8692bc98b18bb7f5ca/78612/previewNav.png 1260w,\n/reponame/static/fac13ecd4e440d8692bc98b18bb7f5ca/669cd/previewNav.png 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Edit one of the blog posts <a name=\"edit-one-of-the-blog-posts\"></a></h3>\n<p>To edit one of the blog posts we must go inside the content folder inside there you will see markdown files.</p>\n<h3>Understand how Gatsby creates our blog posts <a name=\"understand-how-gatsby-creates-our-blog-posts\"></a></h3>\n<p>I’ll walk you through understanding how gatsby does things</p>\n<p>There are a few files with a prefix of gatsby</p>\n<ul>\n<li>gatsby-browser.js\n<ul>\n<li>This is where you put all your styling css files</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>gatsby-config.js\n<ul>\n<li>This is where you put your site’s metadata and gatsby plugins</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>gatsby-node.js\n<ul>\n<li>This is where the magic happens, where your markdown files with the content are put together</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>gatsby-ssr</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Test our understanding how Gatsby creates our blog posts <a name=\"test-our-understanding-how-gatsby-creates-our-blog-posts\"></a></h3>\n<p>To test our understanding how Gatsby creates our blog posts lets take a look inside gatsby-node.js. This is where the magic happens!</p>\n<p>We have 3 functions here</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">createPages</code> This function is avalible to you from the gatsby api. Using this function gives you access to the function createPage.</p>\n<p>This function takes 3 parameters, graphql, actions, and reporter.</p>\n<p>Next we set the method of createPage to actions</p>\n<p>Next we define the path to your blog post template</p>\n<p>After that we create a varible named results and do an await graphql query grabing the nodes and edges</p>\n<p>We check for any error messages</p>\n<p>Next we declare a varible named posts and set it to equal the result’s nodes part</p>\n<p>We next create an if statment to check if there are any “nodes” in other words we are checking if there are any blog posts</p>\n<p>If yes, we want to itterate through all of the blog posts and use the build in function gatsby gives you called createPage and pass that function a object defining the path, component, and the context which contains the post id, previous ,and next post id’s</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">onCreateNode</code> This function</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Connect a headless cms <a name=\"connect-a-headless-cms\"></a></h3>\n<p>Lets now connect a headless cms to our blog. In this tutorial I will be using a headless cms called Sanity.</p>\n<h3>Use Github to host your blog for free <a name=\"use-github-to-host-your-blog-for-free\"></a></h3>\n<h6>Github Client</h6>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">brew install gh</code></pre></div>\n<h6>Git Client</h6>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">brew install git</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Gatsby blog tutorial","date":"September 19, 2015","description":"Tutorial on how to create this gatsby blog"}},"previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/pages/chapter3/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Geology Chapter 3"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"abd35576-2553-5b35-8090-ce9444f324ea","previousPostId":null,"nextPostId":"95d0d493-24a6-5ff6-ac39-2323211448e6"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383","3257411868"]}